Currently, I use four different apps for time management:

Telegram Messenger – for recording and editing time spent in real time
An Android app (available here, now deleted from the Play Store) – for storing data and making info graphics
Google Spreadsheets – for generating reports
Simple Tracker (iOS app) – for displaying daily progress
I think it would be more convenient to have all these functions in one place.

Who will use this app?

I'm primarily building it for myself to fit my personal time management style. There are no different user roles in the app.

Features of my app:

Users can log time using special statements like "0:00 – slept – 8:00", which will automatically be added to the database.
